{"id": "5myjrizpz5uxilif", "type": "text", "content": {"text": "<b>Welcome to the Writer Hacker News Listener: Navigate and analyze Hacker News posts and comments.</b>\n\nWith Hacker News Listener you can:<ul>\n<li>Find news: Pull the latest N posts.</li>\n<li>Ask questions: Explore trending topics, discover recent company and product releases, open-source projects, or job listings.</li>\n<li>Generate a report: Automatically summarize the most popular topics in one click.</li>\n</ul>\nHow the Hacker News Listener works:<ul>\n<li>Data retrieval: The Hacker News API connects to Writer\u2019s graph-based database, known as a Knowledge Graph. This database is accessed dynamically by an LLM through the Writer RAG tool.</li>\n<li>Question answering: The LLM, Palmyra X 004 interprets user queries, calls the Writer RAG tool to retrieve relevant Hacker News posts, and generates responses.</li>\n<li>Report generation: Palmyra X 004 analyzes the N posts stored in the Writer Knowledge Graph and produces a pre-determined structured report highlighting key trends and insights.</li></ul>\nLearn how to <a href=\"https://writer.com/engineering/rag-tool/\" target=\"_blank\">build your own RAG app</a>.", "useMarkdown": "yes"}, "handlers": {}, "isCodeManaged": false, "parentId": "lon4vs20gd3myh7e", "position": 1, "visible": {"binding": "", "expression": true, "reversed": false}}
